programme.title: Arsenal vs Kairat Almaty - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD8
programme.desc: Arsenal’s meeting with Kairat will be just the second time ever that an English side have hosted an opponent from Kazakhstan in European competition, after Manchester United’s 1-0 win over Astana in September 2019 in the UEFA Europa League. This will be Arsenal’s first meeting with Kairat; the Gunners haven’t lost any of the last 11 occasions when facing a team for the first time in European competition, winning 10 of those, since a defeat versus Rennes in March 2019.

programme.desc: PSV have only won one of their previous eight meetings with Bayern Munich, with that lone victory coming in a home match back in October 1999 ; goals from Ruud van Nistelrooy and Luc Nilis. PSV have lost more games against Bayern Munich than versus any other opponent in their European competition history. Indeed, their loss percentage is also higher against Bayern than any other opponent they’ve faced on 5+ occasions in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League.

programme.title: Atlético de Madrid vs Bodø/Glimt - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD8
programme.desc: This will be just the third season in which Atlético Madrid have faced a Norwegian side in major European competition, after 1991-92 v Fyllingen in the Cup Winners’ Cup and 2010-11 v Rosenborg in the UEFA Europa League. Including qualifiers, Atlético Madrid have won all six of their games against Norwegian teams by an aggregate score of 17-4. This will be the first time they have faced a Norwegian opponent during Diego Simeone’s 14-year tenure, however.

programme.title: Sturm Graz vs Brann - UEFA Europa League 2025/2026 - MD8
programme.desc: Sturm Graz and Brann have never met before in European competition – the Austrian side have won both of their previous home games against Norwegian teams, beating FK Haugesund and Bodø/Glimt in August 2019 and August 2025 respectively in European competition’s qualifiers. Brann were knocked out of UEFA Champions League qualifying by Austrian side FC RB Salzburg earlier this season 5-2 on aggregate, their only previous games against a team from Austria.

programme.desc: Bayer Leverkusen and Villarreal will meet for a fifth time in Europe, with the Spanish side winning three of the last four and going unbeaten overall. All four meetings came in the UEFA Europa League between 2011 and 2016. programme.title: Barcelona vs Real Oviedo - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 21 - Mini Match
programme.desc: Barcelona have won seven of their last nine home games against Real Oviedo in LaLiga, losing the most recent one 0-1 in May 2001. The Blaugrana have never lost consecutive home meetings against the Asturian side in the competition's history. Real Oviedo have won four of their last nine games against FC Barcelona in LaLiga, the same number of victories they managed in their previous 24 encounters with the Blaugrana in the competition.

programme.title: Villarreal vs Real Madrid - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 21 - Mini Match
programme.desc: Villarreal have lost four of their last five LaLiga matches against Real Madrid, one more defeat than in their previous 12 matches against them in the competition, losing the last three – only twice before have they lost four or more in a row against them in the top-flight: six in 2002 and five in 2011. Real Madrid have earned points in 21 of their 25 visits to Villarreal in LaLiga – Villarreal have not picked up more home draws against any other opponent in their history in the competition than against the White team.

programme.title: Monaco vs Juventus - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD8
programme.desc: Monaco have only won one of their six games against Juventus in European competition, a 3-2 triumph in April 1998. They have failed to win all four meetings this century, failing to score in three of those. This will be the first meeting between Monaco and Juventus since the semi-finals of the 2016-17 UEFA Champions League, where the Old Lady progressed to the final after winning both legs.

programme.title: Midtjylland vs Dinamo Zagreb - UEFA Europa League 2025/2026 - MD8
programme.desc: FC Midtjylland and Dinamo Zagreb have never faced before – the Danish side last faced Croat opponents in 2002-03 in the UEFA Cup first round, knocking out NK Varazdin 2-1 on aggregate. Dinamo Zagreb have won their two previous away matches in Denmark in European competition, winning 7-2 against a København XI in 1961 in the Fairs Cup and 1-0 against Aalborg BK in 2014 in a UEFA Champions League qualifier.

programme.desc: Basel’s only previous European encounter with a Czechia side came in the 1999 UEFA Intertoto Cup against Zbrojovka Brno, drawing 0-0 at home and winning 4-2 away over two legs in the second round. programme.title: Club Brugge vs Olympique de Marseille - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD8
programme.desc: This will be the third meeting in European competition between Club Brugge and Marseille, with the French side winning 3-0 at home and 1-0 away in the 1992-93 UEFA Champions League group stage, before later beating Milan 1-0 in the final. Marseille are unbeaten in each of their last four away games against Belgian opposition in European competition, while keeping three clean sheets, since a 4-2 loss at Union Saint-Gilloise in the first round of the 1962-63 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup. Club Brugge, meanwhile, have already beaten French side Monaco 4-1 at home in this season’s UEFA Champions League league phase.
